<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<worksheet >
    <title>EL-1 Exponential and Logarithmic Functions</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete all both problems to get M. Complete one problem with progress on the other to get P.</p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <exercise>
      <introduction><p>Given <m>f(x)= 2^{x+3}-1</m>.</p></introduction>
      <task workspace="1.5in"><statement><p>State the domain and range.</p></statement></task>
      <task workspace=".75in"><statement><p>State the intercept(s).</p></statement></task>
      <task workspace="1.5in"><statement><p>State the asymptote(s).</p></statement></task>
      <task workspace="2.5in"><statement><p>Graph <m>f(x)</m></p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
  </page>
  <page>
<exercise>
  <p>An exponential function has a horizontal asymptote at <m>y = 1</m>. 
    The graph of the function passes through the points <m>(-1, 2)</m> and 
    <m>(0, 4)</m>. If the function has the form <m>g(x) = a^{x+b} + c</m> 
    for real numbers <m>a, b</m>, and <m>c</m>, find <m>g(x)</m>.</p>
</exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>